#: ../../apm/set-up-apm/sensitive-data-controls.rst:11
msgid "Sensitive data such as email addresses, credit card information, and social security numbers require careful handling to protect users and ensure compliance with industry standards. By default, Splunk APM does not capture any sensitive information. Splunk APM only receives information that is explicitly sent to it. If sensitive information is sent by mistake, however, Splunk APM provides a number of controls to prevent and mitigate leaks."
